\cf0 \strokec2 Every single Islamic bond (sukuk) currently issued uses these models for pricing at issuance and secondary market valuation, even when the cash flows are structured to look Shariah-compliant. The 
\f2\b pricing engine underneath is still riba-based credit math
\f0\b0 . Islamic finance scholars have largely looked the other way on this because no alternative existed.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

