\f2\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Application 1: On-Chain Sukuk Without Riba Pricing\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Here's what this means concretely for sukuk (Islamic bonds).\
A conventional sukuk pays periodic returns (which are structured as "profit-sharing" or "rent" but are calibrated against LIBOR/SOFR at issuance \'97 making the interest rate implicit in the price). The secondary market trades these using yield-to-maturity calculations which are pure interest math.\
Now consider instead a 
\f2\b Perpetual Credit Sukuk
\f0\b0  built on the Ackerer framework:\
